text: Yelena Gadzhievna Isinbayeva (3 June 1982) is a Russian former pole vaulter. She received two gold medals at the Summer Olympics (in 2004 and 2008). She is a three-time World Champion (in 2005, 2007, and 2013) and the world record holder in the event. Yelena is recognized the greatest female pole-vaulter of all time. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Pole vaulters Category:Olympic gold medalists for Russia Category:World record holders
